'''Richard Ríos Montoya''' (born 2 June 2000) is a Colombian professional [[association football|footballer]] who plays as a [[central midfielder]] for [[Primeira Liga]] club [[S.L. Benfica|Benfica]] and the [[Colombia national football team|Colombia national team]]. Ríos is renowned for his versatility and ball-winning ability.

After beginning his career in Brazil with [[Clube de Regatas do Flamengo|Flamengo]] and [[Guarani Futebol Clube|Guarani]], he moved to [[Sociedade Esportiva Palmeiras|Palmeiras]], where he won the [[2023 Campeonato Brasileiro Série A|Campeonato Brasileiro Série A]] in [[2023 Campeonato Brasileiro Série A|2023]] and the [[2024 Campeonato Paulista|Campeonato Paulista]] in [[2024 Campeonato Paulista|2024]]. In 2025, he transferred to [[S.L. Benfica|Benfica]] and won the [[2025 Supertaça Cândido de Oliveira|Supertaça Cândido de Oliveira]] in his debut season.

Internationally, Ríos debuted for Colombia in 2022 and was part of the squad that finished runners-up at the [[2024 Copa América]].

== Early life ==
Born in [[Vegachí]], Ríos grew up poor in Colombia and saw sports as his path to a better life. He moved to Brazil to follow his dream of becoming a professional player, arriving with just a backpack.<ref>{{cite web |last=V |first=Sanjay Kumar |date=1 July 2025 |title=Nottingham Forest make contact with Tottenham target impressing at the Club World Cup |url=https://tothelaneandback.com/2025/06/28/tottenham-linked-palmeiras-midfielder-richard-rios-wanted-by-nottingham-forest/ |access-date=1 July 2025 |website=To The Lane And Back}}</ref>

==Club career==
===Early career===
Ríos started his career playing [[futsal]] and attracted the interest of [[Clube de Regatas do Flamengo|Flamengo]] during the [[2018 South American Under-20 Football Championship]]. He was invited for a trial period at the Brazilian club and, after two months, Flamengo signed him to their youth team.<ref>{{cite web | url= https://globoesporte.globo.com/futebol/times/flamengo/noticia/flamengo-contrata-talento-colombiano-do-futsal-como-aposta-para-categorias-de-base-no-campo.ghtml | title= Flamengo contrata talento colombiano do futsal como aposta para categorias de base no campo | trans-title=Flamengo sign Colombian futsal talent as a bet for the youth football categories | date= 18 July 2019 | access-date= 3 March 2020 | publisher= [[Grupo Globo|Globoesporte.com]] | language= pt-BR }}</ref>

===Flamengo===
In the beginning of the [[2020 Clube de Regatas do Flamengo season|2020 season]], despite still playing in the youth team, Ríos was promoted to the professional team to play alongside reserve players and other youngsters in the first matches of the [[2020 Campeonato Carioca]].<ref>{{cite web | url= https://colunadofla.com/2020/01/flamengo-deve-utilizar-jovens-do-elenco-principal-como-reforcos-para-a-taca-guanabara/ | title= Flamengo deve utilizar jovens do elenco principal como reforços para a Taça Guanabara | trans-title= Flamengo might use youngsters of the main squad as additions for the Taça Guanabara | date= 2 January 2020 | access-date= 3 March 2020 | publisher= colunadofla.com | language= pt-BR}}</ref> He made his senior debut on 23 January 2020, coming on as a second-half [[Substitute (association football)|substitute]] for [[Matheus Dantas]] in a 1–0 away win over [[CR Vasco da Gama|Vasco da Gama]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.uol.com.br/esporte/futebol/ultimas-noticias/lancepress/2020/01/23/de-rival-de-falcao-no-futsal-a-estreia-no-flamengo-richard-e-elogiado-e-apresentado-por-mauricinho.htm|title=Colombiano do Flamengo foi joia do futsal e se destacou contra Falcão|trans-title=Colombian of Flamengo was a futsal pearl and was a spotlight against Falcão|publisher=[[Universo Online|UOL Esporte]]|language=pt-BR|date=23 January 2020|accessdate=14 February 2023|archive-date=14 February 2023|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20230214190900/https://www.uol.com.br/esporte/futebol/ultimas-noticias/lancepress/2020/01/23/de-rival-de-falcao-no-futsal-a-estreia-no-flamengo-richard-e-elogiado-e-apresentado-por-mauricinho.htm|url-status=dead}}</ref>

Ríos made his [[Campeonato Brasileiro Série A|Série A]] debut on 27 September 2020, replacing [[Guilherme Bala]] in a 1–1 away draw against [[Sociedade Esportiva Palmeiras|Palmeiras]], as Flamengo was heavily impacted due to a [[COVID-19]] outbreak in the squad. The following day, his contract was renewed until December 2021.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://odia.ig.com.br/esporte/flamengo/2020/09/5996817-versatil-contra-o-palmeiras--richard-rios-renova-contrato-com-o-flamengo.html|title=Versátil contra o Palmeiras, Richard Rios renova contrato com o Flamengo|trans-title=Versatile against Palmeiras, Richard Ríos renews contract with Flamengo|publisher=O Dia|language=pt-BR|date=28 September 2020|accessdate=14 February 2023}}</ref>

On 21 June 2021, Ríos signed a contract extension with Flamengo until December 2023, on the same day the club announced his loan to Mexican club [[Mazatlán F.C.|Mazatlán]].<ref>{{cite web | url= https://odia.ig.com.br/esporte/coluna-do-vene/2021/06/6172708-apos-acertar-renovacao-com-richard-rios-flamengo-encaminha-emprestimo-do-volante-ao-futebol-mexicano.html | title= Após acertar renovação com Richard Rios, Flamengo encaminha empréstimo do volante ao futebol mexicano | trans-title= After agreeing renewal with Richard Ríos, Flamengo set loan of defensive midfielder to Mexican football | date= 21 June 2021 | access-date= 22 June 2021 | publisher= O Dia}}</ref>

====Mazatlán (loan)====
On 23 June 2021, Flamengo confirmed the one-year loan deal of Ríos to Mazatlán.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://tntsports.com.br/futebolbrasileiro/Flamengo-confirma-emprestimo-de-Richard-Rios-ao-Mazatlan-do-Mexico-20210623-0007.html|title=Flamengo confirma empréstimo de Richard Ríos ao Mazatlán, do México|trans-title=Flamengo confirm loan of Richard Ríos to Mazatlán, from Mexico|publisher=[[TNT Sports (Brazil)|TNT Sports]]|language=pt-BR|date=23 June 2021|accessdate=14 February 2023}}</ref> He made his debut for the club on 26 July, replacing [[Alfonso Emilio Sánchez|Alfonso Sánchez]] in a 2–0 away win against [[Cruz Azul]].

In September 2021, Ríos suffered a [[knee]] injury,<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.noroeste.com.mx/deportes/futbol/richard-rios-mediocampista-del-mazatlan-fc-sera-baja-de-6-a-8-meses-FX1404025|title=Richard Ríos, mediocampista del Mazatlán FC, será baja de 6 a 8 meses|trans-title=Richard Ríos, Mazatlán FC midfielder, will be out 6 to 8 months|publisher=Noroeste|language=es|date=18 September 2021|accessdate=14 February 2023}}</ref> only returning to action the following April.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://ge.globo.com/futebol/futebol-internacional/noticia/2022/04/23/emprestado-pelo-flamengo-richard-rios-volta-a-jogar-no-mexico-sete-meses-apos-lesao.ghtml|title=Emprestado pelo Flamengo, Richard Ríos volta a jogar no México sete meses após lesão|trans-title=On loan from Flamengo, Richard Ríos is back to action in Mexico seven months after injury|publisher=[[Grupo Globo|ge]]|language=pt-BR|date=23 April 2022|accessdate=14 February 2023}}</ref> In May, after only six matches, Mazatlán opted to not exercise his [[American dollar|US$]] 1 million buyout clause, and he returned to Flamengo.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://ge.globo.com/futebol/futebol-internacional/noticia/2022/05/24/mazatlan-do-mexico-nao-exerce-opcao-de-compra-e-richard-rios-voltara-ao-flamengo.ghtml|title=Mazatlán, do México, não exerce opção de compra, e Richard Ríos voltará ao Flamengo|trans-title=Mazatlán, from Mexico, does not exercise buyout clause, and Richard Ríos will return to Flamengo|publisher=[[Grupo Globo|ge]]|language=pt-BR|date=24 May 2022|accessdate=14 February 2023}}</ref>

===Guarani===
On 4 August 2022, Ríos terminated his contract with Flamengo, and signed a deal with [[Campeonato Brasileiro Série B|Série B]] side [[Guarani FC|Guarani]] until December 2023.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://ge.globo.com/sp/campinas-e-regiao/futebol/times/guarani/noticia/2022/08/04/guarani-anuncia-volante-colombiano-richard-rios.ghtml|title=Volante colombiano Richard Rios encerra vínculo com Flamengo e reforça o Guarani|trans-title=Colombian defensive midfielder Richard Rios ends link with Flamengo and bolsters Guarani|publisher=[[Grupo Globo|ge]]|language=pt-BR|date=4 August 2022|accessdate=14 February 2023}}</ref> He scored his first professional goal on 11 October, netting the winner in a 1–0 home success over [[Clube de Regatas Brasil|CRB]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://correio.rac.com.br/esportes/gol-de-richard-rios-faz-bugre-renascer-1.1300500|title=Gol de Richard Ríos faz Bugre renascer|trans-title=Richard Ríos' goal makes ''Bugre'' be reborn|publisher=Correio Popular|language=pt-BR|date=15 October 2022|accessdate=14 February 2023}}</ref>

In the 2023 season, Ríos became a key unit at ''Bugre''.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://correio.rac.com.br/esportes/richard-rios-e-referencia-do-bugre-no-meio-de-campo-1.1342742|title=Richard Ríos é referência do Bugre no meio de campo|trans-title=Richard Ríos becomes a reference of ''Bugre'' in the midfield|publisher=Correio Popular|language=pt-BR|date=14 February 2023|accessdate=14 February 2023}}</ref>

===Palmeiras===
[[File:Richard-Rios-Palmeiras-Liverpool-abr24-3.jpg|thumb|right|150px|Ríos warming up for [[Sociedade Esportiva Palmeiras|Palmeiras]] in 2024]]
On 28 March 2023, Ríos signed a contract with [[Sociedade Esportiva Palmeiras|Palmeiras]] until the end of 2025, with an option for a further year.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.palmeiras.com.br/noticias/destaque-no-paulista-richard-rios-assina-contrato-e-sera-o-10o-colombiano-da-historia-do-palmeiras/|title=Destaque no Paulista, Richard Ríos assina contrato e será o 10º colombiano da história do Palmeiras|trans-title=Spotlight in the Paulista, Richard Ríos signs contract and will be the 10th Colombian in Palmeiras' history|publisher=SE Palmeiras|language=pt-BR|date=28 March 2023|accessdate=29 March 2023}}</ref> The club paid [[Brazilian real|R$]] 6 million for 60% of his economic rights.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://ge.globo.com/futebol/times/palmeiras/noticia/2023/03/28/palmeiras-anuncia-a-contratacao-de-richard-rios.ghtml|title=Palmeiras anuncia a contratação de Richard Ríos|trans-title=Palmeiras announce the signing of Richard Ríos|publisher=[[Grupo Globo|ge]]|language=pt-BR|date=28 March 2023|accessdate=29 March 2023}}</ref>

Ríos arrived at Palmeiras under the sign of mistrust. Although he did well in Guarani in Paulistão, which aroused the interest of Palmeiras, there was the shadow that he left much to be desired. But the 23-year-old Rios began to steal the show, earning a starting spot, and winning the Brasileirão with the Verdão. In addition, he was the best dribbler in the competition.<ref>{{cite web | url=https://esporte.ig.com.br/parceiros/jogada10/2023-12-16/confira-os-melhores-momentos-de-richard-rios-no-palmeiras-em-2023.html | title=Confira os melhores momentos de Richard Rios no Palmeiras em 2023 | date=17 December 2023 }}</ref>

===Benfica===
On 22 July 2025, [[Primeira Liga]] side [[S.L. Benfica|Benfica]] announced the signing of Ríos on a five-year contract.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.slbenfica.pt/pt-pt/agora/noticias/2025/07/22/futebol-benfica-richard-rios-contratacao|title=Richard Ríos é reforço do Benfica!|trans-title=Richard Ríos is an addition of Benfica!|publisher=SL Benfica|language=pt|date=22 July 2025|accessdate=22 July 2025}}</ref>

==International career==
On 12 October 2023, Ríos made his debut as a substitute for [[Mateus Uribe]] in the 67th minute of a 2–2 draw against Uruguay.<ref name=":0">{{Cite web |title=Colombia – Richard Ríos |url=https://int.soccerway.com/matches/2023/10/12/south-america/wc-qualifying-south-america/colombia/uruguay/4191277/ |access-date=23 July 2025 |website=Soccerway}}</ref> In the [[2024 Copa América]], he was a member of Colombia squad that finished as runner-up to Argentina.

==Style of play==
Ríos is a midfielder who plays in several positions. His physical characteristics allow him to play across the midfield. His technical style includes ball control in restricted spaces and a role in his team's playmaking.<ref name="NFT" />

